In 1882, José Rizal quietly left his homeland, carrying with him not only ambition, but the hopes of a nation yet to awaken. As the ship sailed away from the shores of the Philippines, Rizal looked ahead to an uncertain future—one that would test his courage, intellect, and resolve.
Upon arriving in Spain, José Rizal began his studies and immersed himself in European life. Yet, his journey did not end there. Driven by a deeper desire to expand his knowledge, Rizal soon looked beyond Spain to other centers of learning across Europe.
In Paris, Rizal trained under renowned specialists, sharpening his skills and preparing himself for a greater purpose.